</table><exercise id="eip-624"><problem id="eip-309">
  <para id="eip-418">The marketing team for a business surveyed 100 people and asked them what the maximum price they would pay for the business's product would be.  The results of the survey are given in Table 3 above.  Find the average maximum price a person would pay for the product.
  </para></problem>

</exercise><table id="eip-202" summary="The first row of data in the table says that 3 of the 40 pounds bags of Wonder-Gro that cost $8.00 each were used. The second row of data says that 2 of the 50 pound bags of Scotty's Turf Builder were used. The final row of data says that 3 of the 30 pound bags of Deluxe Dirt that cost $7.50 each were used.">
