</table><exercise id="eip-573"><problem id="eip-550">
  <para id="eip-557">The data in Table 4 above describes the type of soil, number of bags, weight per bag (in pounds), and price per bag of various soils that were used in Oliver's gardening project.  Compute the weighted average given by dividing the total weight of soil used by the total number of bags used.  Write a short sentence interpreting what this weighted average represents.
  </para></problem>


<solution id="eip-idm544316016">
<para id="eip-idm517316064">The weighted average is 38.75 pounds per bag.  This means that if all the bags weighed the same amount and we wanted the total amount of soil used to stay the same, then each bag of soil would have to each weigh 38.75 pounds</para></solution></exercise><exercise id="eip-632"><problem id="eip-474">
  <para id="eip-582">The data in Table 4 above describes the type of soil, number of bags, weight per bag (in pounds), and price per bag of various soils that were used in Oliver's gardening project.  Compute the weighted average given by dividing the total money spent by the total number of bags used.  Write a short sentence interpreting what this weighted average represents.
  </para></problem>


</exercise><exercise id="eip-293"><problem id="eip-idm765170640">
  <para id="eip-idm422017936">The data in Table 4 above describes the type of soil, number of bags, weight per bag (in pounds), and price per bag of various soils that were used in Oliver's gardening project. Compute the weighted average given by dividing the total money spent by the total weight of soil used.  Write a short sentence interpreting what this weighted average represents. </para></problem>



<solution id="eip-idm790426048">
  <para id="eip-idm161772128">The weighted average is $0.21 per pound (rounded to two decimal places).  This means that if Oliver were to spend the same amount of money for each pound of soil used, then he would pay at a rate of approximately 21 cents per pound of soil.
  </para></solution>
</exercise><exercise id="eip-811"><problem id="eip-906">
  <para id="eip-975">Kumar is trying to calculate his final grade in a class.  His grade is determined by 8 quizzes worth 5% each, 4 exams worth 10% each, and homework worth the remaining 20%.  If Kumar had an average quiz score of 91%, an average exam score of 76%, and an average homework score of 80%, then what is Kumar's final grade in the class? </para>
</problem>


</exercise><exercise id="eip-772"><problem id="eip-224">
  <para id="eip-376">Using the information from the previous exercise, find what Kumar's final grade would have been if he got an average of 100% on the homework.  Round your answer to two decimal places if necessary.</para></problem>

<solution id="eip-922">
  <para id="eip-322">Kumar's final grade would become 86.8%.
  </para></solution>
</exercise></section></content>

